subSubSection.paragraph:
CARAPACE (
Fig. 10A–E
). Covered by longitudinal lines and striae between them; anteroventral margin with a widened flange; ventral margin with slight depression before mid-length of body; 80–83 plumose setae per valve, of which the posterior group is longer than median and anterior groups, anterior and posterior setae internally articulated (the real number of setae is not represented in the figures); posterodorsal corner with a notch; posteroventral corner rounded, posterior part bears two groups of short and thick inner spinulae that do not exceed the border.
